  "label": "Heliopause Grotto",
  "description": "Heliopause Grotto is a subsurface cavity cut into Lacrymara’s fault-limned bedrock, its ceilings laminated with glass dust that has sintered into mirror-bright plates. Copper-white twilight filters through narrow fissures, breaking into regimented bands that echo Vesperglass System’s halo geometry across the cave walls. The floor is a shallow, mineral-brined sump whose suspended reflective particulates render depth unreadable and amplify the hushlit gradients. Polished seam-lines run through the chamber like inlaid filaments, marking tectonic stresses with a steady, cold luminescence.",
